  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6811.83 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6800 (-63.8B) and max positive gamma at 6840 (+7.4B), dealers are currently in amplification mode and likely buying this -4.4% dip aggressively as they're short gamma below current levels. The massive negative GEX wall cluster from 6800-6820 creates a volatile zone where dealer hedging will amplify any directional moves, making bounces sharp but potentially short-lived until we clear 6840 where dealers flip to selling pressure. Key inflection points are 6800 (max dealer buying) on the downside and 6840 (dealer selling kicks in) on the upside, with the current spot creating a high-volatility squeeze between these levels.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent swings with strong bounces off 6800 but heavy resistance at 6840.",
